history.content:
169 is definitely more useful for software engineering in general and product management - you get experience working with an actual client (at least with Fox), designing and iterating on a product, and other good practices in software engineering (testing, running meetings, etc.)

I haven't taken 161 but I know it's very specialized knowledge that is cool but not necessarily useful for your goals are.

Workload-wise, again not sure about 161, but with 169 its important to have a group you can work with/count on (you'll be graded fairly for the work you do, but still). It's not a conceptually difficult class, but expect to be working with your teammates and client pretty regularly to meet the regular deadlines of the class.

Hi! I am a graduating senior and deciding between the above two classes. Except I'm having trouble choosing!!!

I don't have previous internship experience and am looking to get a job in product management, design or software engineering upon graduation which makes me think I should take 169 but I also have a pretty tough course load already and am a bit worried I wont enough have time for 169... 

Does the course load of 169 scale similarly to 160?  Is 169 or 161 more valuable for these kinds of careers?

Any advice appreciated!! I've only been in the CS major since, well this summer, so I'm a bit of a newbie :P

My previous CS classes include: the pre-reqs (except 16a which I am taking now), CS 170, CS 160, CS 188

This semester I'm taking: CS 186, EE16a, Cog Sci 127 (Cognitive Neuroscience), CS 161 OR 169

Also have checked and am good to enroll in either, although I have attended more of 161 (already enrolled) than 169
